## Theme / Styling Rules
- **Color Palette Constraint**: The entire UI must strictly adhere to the following color palette. Do not use generic Tailwind colors (e.g., slate, orange, red) unless mapping them to these hex codes:
  - `whisper`: `#f3f2f7` (Light background)
  - `mine-shaft`: `#292929` (Primary dark text, dark mode backgrounds)
  - `flamingo`: `#f25939` (Primary accent, main buttons, highlights)
  - `dusty-gray`: `#949494` (Secondary text, muted elements, borders)
  - `rose-bud`: `#fdb0a1` (Secondary accent, hover states, badges)
  - `spicy-mix`: `#875142` (Darker accents, specific text highlights)
  - `elm`: `#1b6c86` (Information highlights, specific alerts)

- Background: `#f3f2f7` (whisper) instead of `#fffbf7`
- Custom CSS classes defined in `globals.css`:
  - `.flamingo-gradient` — gradient background based on flamingo color
  - `.glass-card` — frosted glass card with flamingo/rose-bud tint
  - `.gradient-text` — flamingo to rose-bud gradient text
  - `.shimmer` — loading skeleton animation
  - `.card-hover` — lift + shadow on hover
  - `.shadow-glow` — flamingo glow shadow
- All interactive elements should have `transition-all duration-200` and `active:scale-95`

